with over 100 000 college student study abroad every year theres bound to be all kind of tall tale urban legend and misinformation swirl around while there may be grain of truth in some of these story below be some common misconception about study abroad misconception # 1 : studying abroad be very expensive truth : in most case it be actually cheaper to study abroad lets say the tuition at your school be $ 5 000 per semester and room and board be another $ 4 000 now add in the additional fee you have such a health insurance book and laundry you be now well over $ 10 000 for the semester well all but one of our program in spain be under $ 10 000 per semester and that include everything except your airfare and spending money tab misconception # 2 : i cant use my financial aid to study abroad truth : in almost all case your federal aid stafford loan pell grant etc can be use to study abroad and in some state you can use your state aid a well it be also not uncommon for your federal aid to increase when you study abroad since some of your school scholarship may not transfer misconception # 3 : host family be all poor and just do it for the money truth : the last thing any study abroad company want to do be have an unhappy student on their program the goal be for the student to be happy so that they will tell their friend what a great time they have if we be put student in bad family in dangerous neighborhood then no one would ever recommend u to their friend since the number of university that endorse our program double over the last year it a pretty sure bet that student be happy with our choice of family misconception # 4 : ill be so busy with schoolwork that i wont get time to see the country im in truth : this one be hysterically funny since your average study abroad student come home with about 400+ photo from a long list of country students have plenty of opportunity to travel and we even take our student on trip to give them a better feel for the country they be in misconception # 5 : i might not graduate on time if i go abroad truth : if you have already use up all of your elective or general education course then it true that you might need to bulk up on course before or after you go abroad if you plan ahead however and leave some elective open to you then you should be fine the clear majority of student who study abroad still graduate in four year despite be away from their home campus for a semester or two misconception # 6 : most of the world hat americans so i wont be safe truth : theres no doubt that there be a lot of people who dont like the american government but that have nothing to do with the american people if you compare the violent crime rate in the united states to that of european australian or asian country you will see that the united states be actually far more dangerous there be some area of south america and africa that be not especially safe but there be also many country on those continent that be incredibly safe go to the u s state department website and check out the crime statistic on the country you be interested in to see how safe it be studying abroad be a once in a lifetime opportunity that every college student should take advantage of before dismiss it due to the bad experience of one friend or rumor you have have hear speak with your study abroad advisor and get the fact i guarantee that once you look at all that study abroad can offer you youll be hop the first flight abroad one organization that help ensure that you have safest unforgettable yet affordable study abroad experience be academic studies abroad here be some of our very popular study abroad programsin the following country : study abroad spain academic studies offer study abroad program in barcelona madrid salamanca and sevilla study abroad england academic studies offer study abroad program in london study abroad italy academic studies offer study abroad program in florence study abroad france academic studies offer study abroad program in aix en provence and avignon [ http : //www academicstu
